      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To adjust your inventory turnover ratio for shrinkage, you first need to calculate your Cost of Goods Sold (COGS) *minus* the value of the lost stock. Then, you divide that adjusted COGS by your average inventory value. This adjustment helps give a more accurate picture of how efficiently you are moving the *actual* available inventory. Keep in mind that a higher shrinkage rate will generally lead to a lower turnover ratio, signaling a potential inventory management issue.",
