      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When items are vanishing like that, it often points to systemic issues rather than obvious external theft. This could be related to improper cycle counting, receiving errors where items are recorded in but never actually stocked, or even internal waste that isn't being properly logged. Sometimes, small, repeated losses are simply lost in the daily operational noise, making them look like \"thin air\" disappearances. You might need to audit specific high-shrink items to see if there's a pattern linked to a particular team or process.",
